6k-Mile 2020 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S Coupe

This 2020 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is an Aventurine Green Metallic-finished coupe that has 6k miles and was optioned from the factory with the Premium and Sport packages. Powered by a twin-turbocharged 3.0L flat-six that drives all four wheels through an eight-speed PDK dual-clutch automatic transaxle, the car is further equipped with Truffle Brown Club leather upholstery, LED-Matrix Design headlights with PDLS+, 20â³ and 21â³ Carrera Classic wheels, a front-axle lift system, a glass sunroof, a surround-view camera system, heated and ventilated 18-way adaptive Sport Plus front seats, Lane Change Assist, a Burmester sound system, and Porsche Communication Management with navigation. This 992.1 4S coupe was acquired by the selling dealer in 2025 and is now offered in Arizona with the ownerâs manual, an accident-free Carfax report, and a California title.

The car is finished in Aventurine Green Metallic and has a glass sunroof, a surround-view camera system, dual exhaust outlets, LED-Matrix Design headlights with PDLS+, fog lights, and front and rear parking sensors.

The 20â³ and 21â³ Carrera Classic wheels are mounted with Goodyear tires. The car is equipped with a front-axle lift system, and braking is handled by High Gloss Black-finished Porsche-script calipers over cross-drilled and ventilated rotors. A brake fluid flush was performed in October 2025.

The heated and ventilated 18-way adaptive Sport Plus front seats are trimmed in Truffle Brown Club leather with contrasting stitching that extends to the center console, dashboard, and door panels. Wood trim accents the cabin, and additional appointments include a Burmester sound system, Lane Change Assist, power-folding mirrors, cruise control, automatic climate control, and Porsche Communication Management with navigation.

The leather-wrapped GT Sport steering wheel features paddle shifters, and it fronts a central 8k-rpm tachometer with an inset speed readout that is flanked by twin LCD screens with configurable displays. A stopwatch is mounted atop the dashboard. The digital odometer indicates 6k miles.

The twin-turbocharged 3.0L flat-six was factory rated at 443 horsepower and 390 lb-ft of torque. Power is routed to all four wheels through an eight-speed PDK dual-clutch automatic transaxle. A replacement battery was installed in November 2024, and an oil change was performed in October 2025.
